 La impedancia es la inversa de esa impedancia 
\begin_inset Formula $Y=\frac{1}{R+jX}$
\end_inset

.
 Haciendo operaciones...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
Y=\frac{1}{R+jX}=\frac{1}{R+jX}\cdot\frac{R-jX}{R-jX}=\frac{R-jX}{R^{2}+X^{2}}=\frac{R}{R^{2}+X^{2}}-j\cdot\frac{X}{R^{2}+X^{2}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

